## Privacy-First Monetization Rules

✅ **Allowed:**
- Gating advanced features (graph view, integrations, etc.)
- Gating collaboration features (requires server)
- Gating premium support
- Gating enterprise features (SSO, audit logs)

❌ **NEVER allowed:**
- Gating core productivity features (notes, tasks, calendar)
- Gating privacy features (encryption, local-first)
- Limiting storage (IndexedDB is unlimited on free tier)
- Ads or selling user data
- Tracking to upsell (no "you used X feature 10 times, upgrade!")
- Annoying upgrade prompts (one subtle banner max)

