## Security Review Process

### For Every PR (Pull Request):

1. **Automated Checks:**
   - [ ] npm audit (no high/critical vulnerabilities)
   - [ ] ESLint security rules pass
   - [ ] TypeScript strict mode (no any types for user input)
   - [ ] Bundle size check (< 200KB)

2. **Manual Review:**
   - [ ] Code review by another developer
   - [ ] Privacy implications assessed
   - [ ] Security checklist completed
   - [ ] UX tested on mobile + desktop

3. **Before Merge:**
   - [ ] All tests pass
   - [ ] Documentation updated
   - [ ] Changelog updated

### For Security-Sensitive Features (Encryption, Auth, etc.):

- [ ] External security audit (hire penetration tester)
- [ ] Threat modeling completed
- [ ] Security documentation written
- [ ] 90-day disclosure policy in place

